The KwaZulu-Natal Department of Sport and Boxing SA has confirmed that boxer Smiso “Gandaganda” Buthelezi died in hospital on Tuesday night. Buthelezi collapsed in the ring near the end of his fight with Siphesihle Mntungwa for the vacant WBF All Africa Lightweight Title in Durban on Sunday and was rushed to hospital. The death resulted from brain damage linked to internal bleeding, according to Boxing SA’s initial statement on Wednesday. The bout was part of Starline Boxing Promotions bill at Greyville Convention Centre and was supported by the department. MEC for Sport, Arts and Culture, Hlengiwe Mavimbela, who attended the event, joined the boxing fraternity on Wednesday in mourning “the untimely passing of the talented Buthelezi”. Mavimbela said in a statement: Boxing SA said it will conduct an independent medical review of the incident and make the results known.